WEBVTT

00:00.875 --> 00:02.375
...6, 7, 8! 1, 2...

00:02.458 --> 00:04.375
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON</i>
<i>"RED BAND SOCIETY"...</i>

00:04.458 --> 00:06.792
Dr. Holzman: SHE IS GOING
TO NEED A HEART TRANSPLANT.

00:06.875 --> 00:10.333
WE FOUND AMPHETAMINES,
NICOTINE, COCAINE, MARIJUANA.

00:10.417 --> 00:11.709
THAT IS GOING TO PUT HER

00:11.792 --> 00:13.083
AT THE BOTTOM OF
THE WAITING LIST.

00:13.166 --> 00:14.959
Jordi: I HAVE OSTEOSARCOMA,
RIGHT LEG.

00:15.041 --> 00:16.291
HANG ON A SECOND.
WHERE ARE YOUR PARENTS?

00:16.375 --> 00:18.792
MY MOM...SHE DIED
LAST YEAR.

00:18.875 --> 00:20.500
WE WILL NEED
SOMEONE FROM YOUR FAMILY

00:20.583 --> 00:22.000
TO SIGN OFF
ON THE TREATMENT.

00:22.083 --> 00:23.792
THIS IS
FROM MY FIRST SURGERY.

00:23.875 --> 00:25.959
AND I WANT YOU TO WEAR IT.
THANKS, LEO.

00:26.041 --> 00:27.792
THAT'S NOT THE BAND I GAVE YOU
LAST NIGHT.

00:27.875 --> 00:29.291
I LOST THE ONE
THAT YOU GAVE ME.

00:29.375 --> 00:30.709
IT SLIPPED OFF
OF MY WRIST.

00:30.792 --> 00:32.792
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

00:40.792 --> 00:45.083
♪ THE ELECTRIC LIGHTS ♪

00:45.166 --> 00:47.667
♪ BLOW MY MIND ♪

00:47.750 --> 00:50.333
Charlie: <i>ONE THING I'VE NOTICED</i>
<i>ABOUT BEING IN A HOSPITAL --</i>

00:50.417 --> 00:52.667
<i>PEOPLE LIE A LOT.</i>

00:52.750 --> 00:54.667
[ DOOR CREAKS ]
<i>THEY LIE</i>
<i>TO MAKE YOU FEEL BETTER.</i>

00:54.750 --> 00:56.834
<i>THEY LIE TO MAKE</i>
<i>THEMSELVES FEEL BETTER.</i>

00:56.917 --> 00:59.166
<i>THEY LIE FOR FUN.</i>

00:59.250 --> 01:01.667
<i>LIES ARE JUST ONE WAY</i>
<i>OF DEALING.</i>

01:01.750 --> 01:02.917
GOT THE STUFF?

01:03.000 --> 01:04.667
DEPENDS.
WHAT DO YOU HAVE FOR ME?

01:04.750 --> 01:07.500
<i>THAT'S ANOTHER.</i>

01:07.583 --> 01:08.834
IS IT THE REAL DEAL?

01:08.917 --> 01:10.667
YOU DON'T BELIEVE ME,
CRACKHEAD?

01:10.750 --> 01:12.125
GIVE IT A WHIFF.

01:12.208 --> 01:13.625
♪ I DON'T WANT TO GO
TO SCHOOL ♪

01:13.709 --> 01:15.333
♪ I JUST WANT TO
BREAK THE RULES ♪

01:15.417 --> 01:17.166
♪ BOYS AND GIRLS
ACROSS THE WORLD ♪

01:17.250 --> 01:18.709
♪ PUTTING ON
OUR DANCING SHOES ♪

01:18.792 --> 01:20.083
[ CHUCKLES ]

01:20.166 --> 01:21.709
SHE'S TOTES INTO YOU.

01:21.792 --> 01:23.166
SAID SHE'D DUMP HER BOYFRIEND
FOR YOUR CANDY ASS.

01:23.250 --> 01:25.458
SERIOUSLY?
SHE TALKED ABOUT MY ASS?

01:25.542 --> 01:27.291
I PARAPHRASED.
NOW WHERE'S MY WEED?

01:28.792 --> 01:30.375
WE HAD A DEAL --

01:30.458 --> 01:32.291
NURSE BRITTANY'S NUMBER
FOR A JOINT.

01:32.375 --> 01:34.959
NOW HAND IT OVER.

01:35.041 --> 01:38.291
WHAT THE HELL?!
THAT'S MY WEED!

01:38.375 --> 01:39.667
AND THAT'S NOT BRITTANY'S
NUMBER, YOU MORON!

01:39.750 --> 01:42.125
SHE DOESN'T EVEN KNOW
THAT YOU EXIST!

01:42.208 --> 01:44.041
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

01:44.125 --> 01:46.542
<i>AND THEN, THERE ARE THE LIES</i>
<i>THAT YOU TELL YOURSELF,</i>

01:46.625 --> 01:49.208
<i>LIKE, "I'M NOT THAT SICK" OR</i>
<i>"A LITTLE SMOKE WON'T KILL ME."</i>

01:49.291 --> 01:51.041
<i>KARA'S GREAT AT THOSE.</i>

01:51.125 --> 01:53.417
THAT'S NOT MINE.
<i>SEE WHAT I MEAN?</i>

01:58.625 --> 02:00.542
MAN, I THOUGHT YOU'D NEVER
GET OUT OF THERE, MAN.

02:00.625 --> 02:03.208
LOOK, I JUST MET
THIS GLAUCOMA DUDE UPSTAIRS

02:03.291 --> 02:04.875
WHO'S LOOKING TO OFFLOAD
THIS BUBBA KUSH,

02:04.959 --> 02:06.792
BUT WE GOT TO ACT FAST,
MAN.

02:06.875 --> 02:08.166
COOL, SOUNDS GOOD.

02:08.250 --> 02:10.333
UM, I GOT TO GO CHECK
ON JORDI FIRST.

02:10.417 --> 02:12.000
OH, COME ON. YOU WERE WITH HIM
ALL NIGHT, MAN.

02:12.083 --> 02:13.834
PLUS, I HAVEN'T HEARD
ANY CODE-BLUE ALARMS

02:13.917 --> 02:15.625
SO I'M PRETTY SURE
AMIGO'S NOT DEAD.

02:15.709 --> 02:17.458
BUT THIS DEAL WILL BE
IF WE DON'T BOOK, MAN.

02:17.542 --> 02:19.792
COME ON.

02:19.875 --> 02:21.291
SERIOUSLY,
ARE YOU TWO STARTING

02:21.375 --> 02:22.917
A CANCER BOY BAND
OR SOMETHING, MAN.

02:23.000 --> 02:26.417
[ CHUCKLES ]
I'LL CATCH UP WITH YOU LATER.

02:26.500 --> 02:29.333
YEAH. LATER.

02:39.583 --> 02:41.792
OH, GOOD.
YOU'RE AWAKE.

02:41.875 --> 02:43.083
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

02:43.166 --> 02:44.917
NERDING OUT ON SUDOKU.

02:45.000 --> 02:46.417
I WANTED TO BE HERE
WHEN YOU WOKE UP

02:46.500 --> 02:48.291
SO YOU WOULDN'T BE ALONE.

02:48.375 --> 02:52.333
BUT IF YOU WANT ME TO GO,
I CAN LEAVE.
NO, NO. DON'T.

02:54.208 --> 02:56.125
WHY <i>ARE</i> YOU ALONE?

02:56.208 --> 02:58.458
I MEAN, USUALLY WHEN PEOPLE
HAVE SURGERY, THEY'RE, LIKE,

02:58.542 --> 03:00.959
BOMBARDED BY EVERY RANDOM
FAMILY MEMBER THEY HAVE.

03:01.041 --> 03:02.625
ARE YOU AN ORPHAN
OR SOMETHING?

03:02.709 --> 03:05.792
I GUESS I KIND OF AM.
I NEVER MET MY DAD.

03:05.875 --> 03:07.333
MY MOM PASSED AWAY
A YEAR AGO.

03:07.417 --> 03:09.875
I'M SO SORRY.
HOW DID SHE DIE?

03:13.208 --> 03:16.500
NEVER MIND.
I SHOULDN'T HAVE ASKED.

03:16.583 --> 03:18.166
NO, IT'S OKAY.
IT'S JUST...

03:18.250 --> 03:19.792
I'M TRYING
TO MOVE PAST IT.

03:19.875 --> 03:21.792
AFTER SHE DIED,
I HAD TO GO LIVE WITH MY ABUELA,

03:21.875 --> 03:23.291
WHO I BARELY EVEN KNOW.

03:23.375 --> 03:25.834
OH, BUT YOU HAVE A GRANDMA.
SO, WHERE'S SHE?

03:25.917 --> 03:28.834
SHE ISN'T EXACTLY A BELIEVER
IN MODERN MEDICINE.

03:28.917 --> 03:30.583
[ MARIACHI MUSIC PLAYS ]

03:30.667 --> 03:33.083
[ GOAT BLEATS ]

03:33.166 --> 03:35.917
[ CHANTING SOFTLY ]

03:36.000 --> 03:37.250
SO, IF NO ONE BELIEVED
YOU WERE SICK,

03:37.333 --> 03:38.667
HOW DID YOU GET
TO THE HOSPITAL?

03:38.750 --> 03:40.208
I CONVINCED MY COUSIN
TO DRIVE ME.

03:40.291 --> 03:42.834
HE WENT TO A DODGERS GAME,
NEVER CAME BACK.

03:42.917 --> 03:44.625
MAYBE
THE DODGERS LOST.

03:44.709 --> 03:46.667
[ CHUCKLES ]
<i>SPOKEN LIKE</i>
<i>A TRUE GIANTS FAN.</i>

03:46.750 --> 03:50.000
OKAY, EVERYTHING
THAT YOU JUST TOLD ME

03:50.083 --> 03:52.333
SUCKS MORE THAN I CAN EVEN
PROCESS RIGHT NOW,

03:52.417 --> 03:54.041
BUT IF YOU EVER
WANT TO TALK...

03:55.333 --> 03:56.917
<i>THERE'S STUMBLING</i>
<i>UPON SOMETHING</i>

03:57.000 --> 03:58.834
<i>YOU DON'T WANT TO SEE,</i>

03:58.917 --> 04:01.166
<i>AND THEN THERE'S LITERALLY</i>
STUMBLING <i>UPON SOMETHING</i>

04:01.250 --> 04:03.500
<i>YOU DON'T WANT TO SEE.</i>
HEY, GUYS.

04:03.583 --> 04:05.834
WHAT'S GOING ON?

04:05.917 --> 04:06.834
HEY. HOW'S P.T.?

04:06.917 --> 04:08.667
LONG AND BORING.

04:08.750 --> 04:10.041
[ CHUCKLES ]

04:10.125 --> 04:12.625
I SHOULD GO.
I CAN'T MISS MY WEIGH-IN.

04:20.959 --> 04:22.875
[ GRUNTS ]

04:22.959 --> 04:25.542
EMMA'S PRETTY GREAT,
ISN'T SHE?

04:25.625 --> 04:27.458
YEAH, SHE IS.

04:28.667 --> 04:29.959
[ GRUNTS ]

04:30.041 --> 04:33.875
YOU KNOW WE, UH...
USED TO BE A THING?

04:33.959 --> 04:35.875
NO, NO, I DIDN'T.

04:35.959 --> 04:40.041
WE BROKE UP A LITTLE WHILE AGO,
BUT IT'S STILL KIND OF...

04:40.125 --> 04:42.291
STILL KIND OF UNFINISHED.

04:42.375 --> 04:44.291
OH. OKAY.

04:46.208 --> 04:47.875
IT'S ALL GOOD.

04:47.959 --> 04:51.125
COOL. THANKS, MAN.

04:51.208 --> 04:53.291
[ SIGHS ]

04:53.375 --> 04:56.375
<i>FOR THE RECORD --</i>
<i>IT COULD NOT BE LESS GOOD.</i>

04:59.667 --> 05:02.417
I'M INN-O-CENT!
I WANT TO CALL MY LAWYER.

05:02.500 --> 05:04.583
PLUS, ALSO,
YOU HAVE TO READ ME MY RIGHTS.

05:04.667 --> 05:06.750
FINE. YOU HAVE THE RIGHT
TO REMAIN SILENT.

05:06.834 --> 05:08.917
YOU CAN'T PROVE ANYTHING.
WAIT!
UH-HUH.

05:09.000 --> 05:10.750
ARE YOU GONNA CALL
MY PARENTS?
SILENT.

05:10.834 --> 05:12.959
AND, NO, I'M NOT GONNA CALL
YOUR PARENTS.

05:13.041 --> 05:14.917
I MET YOUR PARENTS, AND
THEY'RE A BIGGER PAIN
IN MY ASS THAN YOU.

05:15.000 --> 05:16.417
OH, BUT I WILL
HAVE THE ORDERLIES

05:16.500 --> 05:18.417
STRAP YOU TO THAT BED
IF I HAVE TO.

05:18.500 --> 05:20.417
[ SCOFFS ]
WHATEVER GETS YOU OFF.

05:20.500 --> 05:23.166
WHY ARE YOU
STILL TALKING?

05:23.250 --> 05:26.250
BECAUSE I HAVE THE SHAKES,
AND NOT IN THE FUN KIND OF WAY.

05:26.333 --> 05:29.750
MY HEAD IS KILLING ME,
AND FOR SOME REASON, I'M --

05:29.834 --> 05:32.250
I'M HOT AND I'M COLD
AND THEN I'M HOT AGAIN.

05:32.333 --> 05:34.792
THAT'S BECAUSE
YOU'RE IN WITHDRAWAL.

05:34.875 --> 05:35.834
WITHDRAWAL?

05:35.917 --> 05:37.625
YES.
YOU'RE A DRUG ADDICT.

05:37.709 --> 05:40.458
[ SCOFFS ]
NO, I'M NOT.

05:40.542 --> 05:41.959
I JUST LIKE PILLS --

05:42.041 --> 05:43.959
PILLS TO STAY UP,
PILLS TO FALL ASLEEP,

05:44.041 --> 05:45.875
AND PILLS
TO HELP ME STUDY.

05:45.959 --> 05:47.709
YOUR SECOND DRUG TEST
IS TODAY AT 4:00.

05:47.792 --> 05:49.375
AND IF YOUR PEE
DOES NOT COME BACK

05:49.458 --> 05:51.041
CLEANER THAN
A MORMON VARIETY SHOW,

05:51.125 --> 05:53.166
IT'LL BE A DING AGAINST YOU
GETTING A NEW HEART,

05:53.250 --> 05:55.375
WHICH IS WHY
YOU ARE NOT LEAVING THIS ROOM

05:55.458 --> 05:58.166
UNTIL THE LITTLE MAN
COMES AROUND WITH A PEE JAR.

05:59.750 --> 06:02.834
WELL, DR. DREW SAYS THAT,
IN ORDER TO STAY SOBER,

06:02.917 --> 06:05.333
I NEED A FRIEND,
SOMEONE TO TALK TO.

06:05.417 --> 06:06.959
WELL,
YOU GOT CHARLIE.

06:07.041 --> 06:10.125
UM, VEGGIE-BOY ISN'T MUCH OF
A CONVERSATIONALIST.

06:10.208 --> 06:12.458
[ SCOFFS ]
<i>I PREFER VEGGIE YOUNG-ADULT.</i>

06:12.542 --> 06:14.291
YOU'RE NOT MUCH
OF A LISTENER.

06:14.375 --> 06:16.333
THIS IS SO UNFAIR!

06:16.417 --> 06:18.500
EVERYONE ELSE GETS TO DO
WHATEVER THEY WANT.

06:18.583 --> 06:19.875
EMMA'S NOT EVEN SICK,

06:19.959 --> 06:21.583
AND SHE'S TREATED LIKE
A FRICKING PRINCESS!

06:21.667 --> 06:25.542
MNH-MNH!
ALL I ASK IS THIS ONE TINY,
LITTLE THING.

06:25.625 --> 06:28.792
FINE! ONE FRIEND.

06:43.083 --> 06:46.667
SAVING UP
FOR THE BIG EARTHQUAKE?

06:46.750 --> 06:48.917
I'M MAKING
KRISPIE TREATS.

06:49.000 --> 06:52.166
NOT FOR ME, FOR JORDI.
HE'S HAVING A ROUGH DAY.

06:52.250 --> 06:53.834
I THOUGHT I'D DO
SOMETHING NICE FOR HIM.

06:53.917 --> 06:55.709
IS HE IN KINDERGARTEN?

06:57.166 --> 07:00.959
I'M KIDDING.
IT'S REALLY NICE OF YOU.

07:01.041 --> 07:03.542
I'M IN.
HOW CAN I HELP?

07:03.625 --> 07:05.375
<i>YOU</i> WANT TO HELP?

07:05.458 --> 07:07.041
SURE.
HE'S A FELLOW RED BANDER.

07:07.125 --> 07:09.041
IF HE'S HAVING A ROUGH DAY,
I WANT TO BE THERE FOR HIM.

07:09.125 --> 07:11.208
WELL, IN THAT CASE,
I COULD, UH --

07:11.291 --> 07:12.709
I COULD USE
SOME MORE BUTTER.

07:12.792 --> 07:15.583
BUTTER.
COMING RIGHT UP.

07:25.333 --> 07:28.500
[ HUMMING ]

07:30.291 --> 07:32.542
WHY DO OUR FILES
LOOK LIKE A...

07:32.625 --> 07:34.291
PRIDE PARADE?

07:34.375 --> 07:36.375
THESE PATIENT FILES ARE FILLED
WITH SO MUCH SADNESS.

07:36.458 --> 07:40.083
I WANTED TO CHEER 'EM UP
WITH SOME HAPPY LABELS.

07:40.166 --> 07:41.750
THERE'S A BALLOON
OVER THE "I."

07:41.834 --> 07:43.166
IT'S CALLED
"BIRTHDAY" FONT.

07:43.250 --> 07:44.917
WHO DOESN'T LOVE
THEIR BIRTHDAY?

07:45.000 --> 07:46.625
BIRTHDAY PARTY,
BIRTHDAY PRESENTS,

07:46.709 --> 07:48.291
BIRTHDAY PEDICURE.

07:48.375 --> 07:50.583
NOW I'M STARTING TO WISH
I WAS NEVER BORN.

07:50.667 --> 07:53.625
GOOD MORNING.
DO NOT GIVE ME THAT LOOK.

07:53.709 --> 07:55.500
I DIDN'T SLEEP WELL
LAST NIGHT.

07:55.583 --> 07:57.083
MM, IS THAT RIGHT?

07:57.166 --> 07:59.458
DR. McANDREW, YOU'RE WEARING
YOUR NAVY-BLUE TIE.

07:59.542 --> 08:01.417
YES. SO?

08:01.500 --> 08:04.959
SO, THAT MEANS YOU MUST HAVE
HAD SEX LAST NIGHT.

08:05.041 --> 08:06.083
WHAT?

08:07.417 --> 08:09.166
WELL, YOU WEAR
YOUR YELLOW TIE FOR SURGERY

08:09.250 --> 08:10.417
AND YOUR CUTE MADRAS BOW TIE
ONLY COMES OUT

08:10.500 --> 08:11.792
WHEN YOUR
RELATIVES VISIT

08:11.875 --> 08:13.917
AND THE BLUE TIE MEANS
YOU HAD SEX.

08:14.917 --> 08:16.000
[ LAUGHS ]

08:21.041 --> 08:23.458
YOU TOLD ME A GOOD NURSE

08:23.542 --> 08:25.625
KNOWS THE ATTENDING PHYSICIAN
INSIDE AND OUT.

08:25.709 --> 08:28.792
[ SIGHS ] DID YOU CHECK
ON COURTNEY LOVE RECENTLY?

08:28.875 --> 08:30.041
I'M LETTING
THAT SLEEPING BEAST LIE.

08:30.125 --> 08:31.709
LAST TIME I WOKE HER UP,

08:31.792 --> 08:34.542
SHE SCREAMED AT ME
FOR RUINING HER SHOPPING DREAM

08:34.625 --> 08:37.125
WITH BRANDI FROM
"THE REAL HOUSEWIVES."

08:37.208 --> 08:38.458
[ CHUCKLES ]
OH, I DO LOVE THAT SHOW.

08:38.542 --> 08:39.792
SERIOUSLY, THOUGH,
WHO DOESN'T?

08:39.875 --> 08:41.125
[ ALARM BEEPS ]

08:41.208 --> 08:44.041
SPEAK OF THE DEVIL.

08:44.125 --> 08:47.208
[ SUPER WILD HORSES'
"MESS AROUND" PLAYS ]

08:49.917 --> 08:51.125
♪ I GOT A MESSAGE FOR YOU ♪

08:51.208 --> 08:53.375
OH, MY GOD! HELLO?!

08:53.458 --> 08:54.542
♪ IT GOES, "OOH, OOH, OOH" ♪
WE'RE IN THE MIDDLE
OF SOMETHING.

08:54.625 --> 08:56.333
♪ WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO? ♪

08:56.417 --> 08:59.000
<i>NOT EXACTLY HOW I IMAGINED</i>
<i>MY FIRST THREE-WAY.</i>

08:59.083 --> 09:02.542
<i>BUT I'M NOT GONNA LIE,</i>
<i>I'LL TAKE IT.</i>

09:02.625 --> 09:06.375
♪ I'M GONNA MESS AROUND ♪

09:08.875 --> 09:10.291
WHAT THE HELL
IS WRONG WITH YOU?

09:10.375 --> 09:12.375
YOU COULD HAVE SCARRED
THIS POOR CHILD FOR LIFE.

09:12.458 --> 09:14.041
OVERREACTING MUCH?

09:14.125 --> 09:17.250
I NEEDED <i>SOMETHING</i>
TO KEEP MY MIND OFF OF DRUGS.

09:17.333 --> 09:18.917
PLUS, IT'S JUST SEX.

09:19.000 --> 09:21.041
OR HAS IT BEEN SO LONG
THAT YOU'VE FORGOTTEN?

09:21.125 --> 09:23.041
OKAY. OKAY,
FUN AND GAMES ARE OVER.

09:23.125 --> 09:24.917
BOOTY CALL'S
GONNA PACK UP HIS BALLS

09:25.000 --> 09:26.417
AND GO HOME,
AND YOU'RE GONNA GET DRESSED

09:26.500 --> 09:28.458
AND MEET ME AT THE NURSES'
STATION IN 10 MINUTES.

09:28.542 --> 09:31.917
CONGRATULATIONS.
I'M YOUR NEW SOBER COMPANION.

09:32.000 --> 09:34.875
WHAT?
MM-HMM.

09:34.959 --> 09:36.291
BYE, BABY.

09:45.500 --> 09:49.083
[ MEIKO'S "STUCK ON YOU" PLAYS ]

10:02.000 --> 10:05.917
♪ DO, DO-DO-DO-DO, DO ♪

10:06.000 --> 10:08.417
♪ DO-DO-DO-DO ♪

10:08.500 --> 10:10.417
♪ DO-DO-DO-DO ♪

10:10.500 --> 10:12.291
♪ OOH, OOH ♪
ADMITTEDLY,
IT'S NOT MY BEST LOOK.

10:12.375 --> 10:14.500
♪ 'CAUSE YOU ARE THE ONE ♪
IT'S JUST A LITTLE SMALL.

10:14.583 --> 10:15.834
♪ I COULD SEE HAVING FUN WITH ♪
MY SISTER JUST SENT ME
ALL THESE.

10:15.917 --> 10:17.750
I THINK THIS ONE
MIGHT EVEN BE HERS.

10:17.834 --> 10:19.291
♪ NOT JUST FOR THE NIGHT,
BUT FOR THE REST OF MY LIFE ♪

10:19.375 --> 10:21.000
I'M LEO.

10:21.083 --> 10:23.625
EMMA.
NICE TO MEET YOU.

10:23.709 --> 10:25.458
♪ YOU ARE THE ONE I COULD
NEVER BE DONE WITH ♪

10:25.542 --> 10:28.166
FOR WHAT IT'S WORTH, YOU, UH --
YOU HAVE A NICE HEAD.

10:28.250 --> 10:29.792
♪ I WANT YOU TONIGHT
AND FOR THE REST ♪
I DON'T THINK YOU NEED
ANY HATS AT ALL.

10:29.875 --> 10:30.959
[ CHUCKLES ]

10:31.041 --> 10:34.333
♪ OF MY LIFE ♪

10:34.417 --> 10:36.458
♪ DO, DO-DO-DO-DO, DO ♪
LOOKS WAY BETTER ON YOU.

10:36.542 --> 10:37.834
[ CHUCKLES ]
Dash:YO!

10:39.208 --> 10:41.125
NOT EVEN GONNA ASK.

10:41.208 --> 10:42.458
THEY'RE FOR EMMA.

10:42.542 --> 10:44.834
OH, THUMBELINA
HAS AN APPETITE?

10:44.917 --> 10:47.208
WE'RE BAKING SOMETHING
FOR JORDI.
SHOULD HAVE KNOWN.

10:47.291 --> 10:49.291
TO THE J-MAN.D BACK

10:49.375 --> 10:50.750
I'M WORKING
A DEEPER GAME.

10:50.834 --> 10:52.375
IT'S ALL PART OF MY PLAN
TO GET BACK WITH EMMA.

10:52.458 --> 10:54.291
SINCE WHEN DO YOU WANT TO
GET BACK WITH EMMA?

10:54.375 --> 10:55.917
SINCE NOW.

10:56.000 --> 10:57.709
OH, JORDI GETS TO KEEP THE LEG,
SO YOU KEEP THE GIRL?

10:57.792 --> 10:59.375
THAT SORT OF THING?
YOU GOT PROBLEMS, DASH,

10:59.458 --> 11:00.959
ARE THE LEAST OF THEM.

11:01.041 --> 11:03.500
LOOK, MAN, I'M ALL FOR
A STEVE AND D.J. REUNION,

11:03.583 --> 11:05.208
BUT I'M JUST SAYING,
YOU KNOW,

11:05.291 --> 11:06.792
I FEEL LIKE YOUR NEW
ROOMMATE MAY HAVE OTHER PLANS.

11:06.875 --> 11:08.083
I ALREADY SQUARED THINGS
WITH HIM,

11:08.166 --> 11:09.208
AND HE'S NOT MOVING IN
ON HER.

11:09.291 --> 11:11.500
BECAUSE <i>HE</i> SAID SO?

11:11.583 --> 11:13.875
NO,
BECAUSE <i>I</i> SAID SO.

11:16.917 --> 11:20.083
<i>YOU'RE LOOKING AT THE ONE THING</i>
<i>IN A HOSPITAL</i>

11:20.166 --> 11:23.500
<i>THAT NEVER LIES --</i>
<i>A PET SCAN.</i>

11:23.583 --> 11:25.667
<i>THINK OF IT LIKE</i>
<i>AN ELECTORAL MAP.</i>

11:25.750 --> 11:29.333
<i>RIGHT NOW RED'S FILIBUSTERING</i>
<i>THE CRAP OUT OF JORDI'S LEG.</i>

11:29.417 --> 11:32.000
OKAY. SO, WHAT THESE SCANS
ARE SHOWING US

11:32.083 --> 11:35.667
IS THAT YOUR CANCER
IS NOT AN OSTEOSARCOMA.

11:35.750 --> 11:37.750
IT'S SOMETHING CALLED
A EWING'S SARCOMA.

11:37.834 --> 11:39.083
WHAT'S THE DIFFERENCE?

11:39.166 --> 11:40.667
THEY BOTH START
IN THE BONE,

11:40.750 --> 11:42.333
BUT THEY'RE TWO COMPLETELY
DIFFERENT TYPES OF TUMORS.

11:42.417 --> 11:44.834
AND FOR THAT REASON, WE NEED
TO TREAT THEM DIFFERENTLY.

11:46.417 --> 11:47.542
[ SIGHS ]

11:47.625 --> 11:49.166
SO,
WHEN DO I START CHEMO?

11:49.250 --> 11:52.542
UH...WELL,
I DID GO AHEAD

11:52.625 --> 11:54.542
AND CONTACT YOUR GRANDMOTHER
IN MEXICO, AND --

11:54.625 --> 11:56.959
DOES SHE FINALLY BELIEVE
I HAVE CANCER?

11:57.041 --> 11:59.291
SHE'S PRETTY COMMITTED TO

11:59.375 --> 12:01.083
THE WHOLE "DEMONS IN
YOUR LEG" THING.

12:01.166 --> 12:03.750
AND AFTER A LOT OF SCREAMING
IN SPANISH,

12:03.834 --> 12:06.417
SHE, UH, WANTS TO RETURN YOU
TO HER FAITH HEALER.

12:06.500 --> 12:08.375
I CAN'T GO BACK THERE,
DR. McANDREW.

12:08.458 --> 12:09.667
I'M IN A TOUGH SPOT.

12:09.750 --> 12:11.291
I NEED SOMEONE
FROM YOUR FAMILY

12:11.375 --> 12:13.125
TO SIGN OFF
ON THIS TREATMENT.

12:13.208 --> 12:15.417
SINCE YOUR MOM
PASSED AWAY,

12:15.500 --> 12:16.750
MAYBE IF WE TRY
AND CONTACT YOUR DAD?

12:16.834 --> 12:17.959
GREAT IDEA.
I'D LOVE TO MEET HIM.

12:21.709 --> 12:25.125
OKAY. UM...

12:25.208 --> 12:26.417
ALL RIGHT,
WELL, LISTEN.

12:26.500 --> 12:28.458
SOCIAL SERVICES
NOW HAS YOUR CASE.

12:28.542 --> 12:31.083
THEY CAN HELP YOU FIGURE OUT
WHAT YOUR NEXT STEP IS GONNA BE.

12:31.166 --> 12:32.417
I ALREADY KNOW
WHAT MY NEXT STEP IS.

12:32.500 --> 12:33.792
I WANT TO BECOME
AN EMANCIPATED MINOR

12:33.875 --> 12:35.500
SO I CAN MAKE MY OWN
MEDICAL DECISIONS.

12:35.583 --> 12:37.583
JORDI, YOU'RE TOO YOUNG
TO BE DOING THAT.

12:37.667 --> 12:39.834
YOU CAN BE EMANCIPATED AT 14
IN THE STATE OF CALIFORNIA.

12:41.500 --> 12:44.250
NO MATTER WHAT HAPPENS, YOU'RE
STILL GONNA BE MY DOCTOR, RIGHT?

12:44.333 --> 12:46.750
YOU CAN'T GET RID OF ME
THAT EASY.

12:48.709 --> 12:50.166
ALL RIGHT.

12:50.250 --> 12:53.000
ALTHOUGH,
I'M LEAVING.

12:53.083 --> 12:55.583
[ CHUCKLES ]
HANG IN THERE, OKAY?

12:58.000 --> 12:59.834
[ SIGHS ]

13:03.583 --> 13:06.166
OKAY,
YOU ARE ALL SET.

13:06.250 --> 13:09.500
ENOUGH TO KEEP YOUR DRINK ON
ALL DAY.

13:09.583 --> 13:11.041
CAN YOU DO ME A FAVOR?

13:12.667 --> 13:15.125
I GOT TO CONVINCE THE DOCTORS
TO GIVE ME A WEEKEND PASS.

13:15.208 --> 13:17.166
CAN YOU JUST TELL THEM
MY BATTERY'S FULLY CHARGED.

13:17.250 --> 13:19.333
WHY WOULD I DO THAT, DASH?
YOU'RE DEHYDRATED.

13:19.417 --> 13:21.834
AND YOU'VE SKIPPED YOUR LAST TWO
BREATHING TREATMENTS.

13:21.917 --> 13:23.333
BECAUSE I'M ABOUT
TO PULL THE TRIGGER

13:23.417 --> 13:25.458
ON SOME SISYPHUS TICKETS
IN SAN DIEGO.

13:25.542 --> 13:27.166
I GOT SOME
ILL-ASS SEATS.

13:27.250 --> 13:29.000
I'M JUST TRYING TO SURPRISE
MY BOY, LEO. THAT ALL.

13:29.083 --> 13:30.500
FOR STARTERS,
YOU CAN'T GO TO A CONCERT.

13:30.583 --> 13:34.000
MUSIC VENUES ARE PETRI DISHES
FOR INFECTION.

13:34.083 --> 13:36.792
PLUS, THIS FEELS LIKE
AN EXTREME PURCHASE,

13:36.875 --> 13:39.458
AND THIS IS COMING FROM A GIRL
WHO ONCE SPENT $200

13:39.542 --> 13:42.291
ON LIP LINERS, SO...
IT'S NOT EVEN LIKE THAT.

13:42.375 --> 13:43.792
I JUST THOUGHT ME AND LEO
COULD USE SOME TIME

13:43.875 --> 13:46.667
OUTSIDE OF THIS DUNGEON.

13:46.750 --> 13:49.625
AWAY FROM JORDI?

13:51.208 --> 13:52.375
OH...

13:52.458 --> 13:54.125
LEO BROKE YOUR
LITTLE BRO-HEART, HUH?

13:54.208 --> 13:56.041
THAT'S SO SWEET.

13:56.125 --> 13:58.542
BROKE MY BRO-- WHAT ARE YOU --
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

13:58.625 --> 14:00.375
IT'S OKAY. IT'S OKAY.
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

14:00.458 --> 14:03.542
BROMANCES CAN HURT JUST AS MUCH
AS REGULAR ROMANCES.

14:03.625 --> 14:05.709
I USED TO HAVE A WOMANCE
WITH MY FRIEND CHABLEY,

14:05.792 --> 14:08.041
HUNG OUT EVERY DAY
AT FROYO LAND,

14:08.125 --> 14:09.458
HMM,
BROKE CURFEW TOGETHER,

14:09.542 --> 14:12.166
STAR-69'd ANYBODY
WHO PRANKED US --

14:12.250 --> 14:13.500
YOU 69'd?

14:13.583 --> 14:14.792
MEANT SOMETHING
MUCH DIFFERENT.

14:14.875 --> 14:16.333
SIMPLER TIMES, DASH.
SIMPLER TIMES.

14:16.417 --> 14:19.667
MY POINT IS,
CHABLEY AND I WERE INSEPARABLE.

14:19.750 --> 14:21.709
AND THEN,
DAWN TRIMMER HAPPENED.

14:21.792 --> 14:24.417
DAWN AND HER STUPID
IN-GROUND POOL. NEXT THING
I KNEW, I WAS REPLACED.

14:24.500 --> 14:27.834
TRADED UP FOR A POOL.
THAT'S COLD.
BUT GUESS WHAT.

14:27.917 --> 14:29.667
THREE WEEKS LATER,
CHABLEY CAUGHT HER BOYFRIEND

14:29.750 --> 14:31.542
SKINNY-DIPPING WITH DAWN
IN THAT STUPID IN-GROUND POOL.

14:31.625 --> 14:35.834
AND YOU KNOW WHO SHE CALLED
TO DROWN HERSELF IN FROYO WITH?

14:35.917 --> 14:37.542
OKAY, SO, YOU'RE SAYING

14:37.625 --> 14:39.583
I SHOULD JUST LET THIS
WHOLE THING PLAY ITSELF OUT?

14:39.667 --> 14:42.083
I'M SAYING
YOU CAN'T BUY LOVE.

14:42.166 --> 14:45.083
AND REAL FRIENDS
WILL ALWAYS NEED YOU.

14:45.166 --> 14:47.834
OKAY, FIRST OF ALL,
I DON'T LOVE LEO.

14:49.000 --> 14:50.458
AND I GOT A HUNDRED
DIFFERENT WAYS

14:50.542 --> 14:51.959
TO PROVE THAT TO YOU
WHENEVER YOU'RE DOWN.

14:52.041 --> 14:53.542
OKEYDOKE.

14:53.625 --> 14:55.125
GOOD TALK.

14:56.709 --> 14:58.959
MORE LIKE 68.

14:59.041 --> 15:02.125
DO IT WITH ME,
AND I'LL OWE YOU ONE.

15:02.208 --> 15:04.375
NEXT, WE POUR THE BUTTER
OVER THE MARSHMALLOWS

15:04.458 --> 15:06.875
AND STIR SLOWLY.
YOU'D THINK THAT WOULD BE
IMPOSSIBLE TO SCREW UP,

15:06.959 --> 15:08.375
BUT I'VE BEEN KNOWN
TO BURN TOAST.

15:08.458 --> 15:09.792
[ CULTS'
"YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN" PLAYS ]

15:09.875 --> 15:11.959
<i>THIS IS THE DOCTORS' LOUNGE --</i>

15:12.041 --> 15:13.208
<i>NO PATIENTS ALLOWED.</i>
♪ I, I CAN'T
TAKE THINGS SLOWLY ♪

15:13.291 --> 15:14.875
<i>THEY'RE BREAKING THE RULES.</i>

15:14.959 --> 15:17.041
<i>THAT'S THE KIND OF RECKLESS FUN</i>
<i>WE GET INTO HERE</i>

15:17.125 --> 15:19.667
<i>AT OCEAN PARK HOSPITAL.</i>

15:19.750 --> 15:21.291
IS IT WEIRD TO COOK
BUT NOT EAT?
♪ COME, LET AWAY,
THAT'S WHAT THEY ALL DO ♪

15:21.375 --> 15:23.250
SEEMS LIKE
IT WOULD BE TORTURE.

15:23.333 --> 15:25.834
IT'S ACTUALLY
KIND OF COMFORTING.

15:25.917 --> 15:27.959
YOU KNOW, IT'S A WAY
TO BE AROUND FOOD,

15:28.041 --> 15:29.834
TO FIXATE ON FOOD.
♪ HELP ME,
'CAUSE I'M FEELING SHAKY ♪

15:29.917 --> 15:31.000
TO CONTROL IT.

15:32.375 --> 15:34.417
I MEAN, NOT THAT I'M
SAYING YOU'RE A CONTROL
FREAK OR ANYTHING --

15:34.500 --> 15:37.583
DO NOT START.
YOU LIKE COMEDIES,
BUT NOT ROMANTIC COMEDIES.

15:37.667 --> 15:40.250
YOU LIKE ACTION MOVIES, BUT
NOT WHEN THEY TRY TO BE FUNNY.

15:40.333 --> 15:42.417
I'M SPECIFIC, ALL RIGHT?
THERE'S A DIFFERENCE.

15:42.500 --> 15:45.250
♪ 'CAUSE I AM AFRAID
OF THE LIGHT ♪

15:45.333 --> 15:50.250
♪ YEAH,
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN ♪

15:50.333 --> 15:51.750
♪ AND I CAN'T SLEEP ALONE
AT NIGHT ♪

15:51.834 --> 15:54.250
WE SHOULD, UM --

15:54.333 --> 15:56.417
WE SHOULD GET THESE INTO A PAN
BEFORE THEY COOL.
♪ YEAH, YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN ♪

16:06.542 --> 16:07.959
IT'S JUST A TIE,
BRITTANY.

16:08.041 --> 16:09.667
HMM? WHAT? NOTHING.

16:09.750 --> 16:11.166
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

16:11.250 --> 16:12.959
OKAY, WE NEED TO FOLLOW UP
WITH SOCIAL SERVICES.

16:13.041 --> 16:15.125
I WANT TO GET JORDI
STARTED ON CHEMO ASAP.

16:15.208 --> 16:16.792
I'M ALL OVER IT.

16:16.875 --> 16:18.166
BALLPARK FIGURE --

16:18.250 --> 16:20.041
I MEAN, UH,
HOW LONG DO YOU THINK

16:20.125 --> 16:22.792
JORDI WILL REALISTICALLY BE
OCCUPYING MY BED IN THE SWAMP?

16:22.875 --> 16:24.333
WE ARE NOT DISCUSSING

16:24.417 --> 16:26.125
A PATIENT'S MEDICAL CONDITION
WITH YOU, DASH.

16:26.208 --> 16:28.000
I'M JUST SAYING, MAN,
YOU KNOW,

16:28.083 --> 16:31.667
I'M DOWN TO MOVE IN IF JORDI
SOMEHOW DOESN'T PULL THROUGH.

16:31.750 --> 16:34.000
OKAY. WE'LL, UH --
WE'LL NOTE THAT IN YOUR FILE.

16:34.083 --> 16:35.125
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

16:39.458 --> 16:42.333
HEY.
HEY.

16:42.417 --> 16:43.834
[ BOTH CHUCKLING ]

16:43.917 --> 16:45.917
♪ D-D-DOWN LOW ♪

16:46.000 --> 16:47.875
[ CHUCKLES ]

16:49.583 --> 16:51.000
YOU, UH...

16:51.083 --> 16:53.166
YOU SNUCK OUT EARLY
THIS MORNING.

16:53.250 --> 16:56.667
WELL, I WANTED TO AVOID
THAT AWKWARD MOMENT.

16:56.750 --> 16:58.125
<i>TOO LATE, SISTER.</i>

16:58.208 --> 17:02.834
LOOK, I HAD AN AMAZING TIME,
BUT IT'S A --

17:02.917 --> 17:05.208
IT'S A LITTLE STRANGE THAT
YOU TRACKED ME DOWN AT WORK.

17:05.291 --> 17:08.166
I AM VISITING MY SON.

17:08.250 --> 17:10.083
I'M SORRY.
WHO'S YOUR SON?

17:10.166 --> 17:11.250
Jordi: MOM?

17:14.291 --> 17:16.709
JO-JO.

17:21.625 --> 17:23.750
<i>DID NOT SEE THAT COMING.</i>

17:25.375 --> 17:28.166
MIJO, WHAT HAVE THEY DONE
TO YOU? YOU'RE SO THIN.

17:28.250 --> 17:29.917
I'M SICK, MOM.

17:31.000 --> 17:32.875
THIS IS MY DOCTOR.

17:34.750 --> 17:37.417
[ CHUCKLES ]
HE'S YOUR DOCTOR?

17:39.583 --> 17:41.500
YEAH.
YEAH, YOU KNOW HIM?

17:43.083 --> 17:44.834
OF COURSE
I DON'T KNOW HIM.

17:44.917 --> 17:46.875
I KNOW NOTHING.
NOBODY TELLS ME ANYTHING.

17:46.959 --> 17:48.291
YOUR ABUELA CALLS
OUT OF THE BLUE

17:48.375 --> 17:49.375
AND SAYS SOMETHING'S WRONG
WITH YOUR LEG

17:49.458 --> 17:50.875
AND WOULD I CHECK ON YOU.

17:50.959 --> 17:53.583
WHY DIDN'T ANYONE HERE
CALL ME?

17:55.083 --> 17:56.583
'CAUSE YOU'RE DEAD.

17:58.458 --> 18:00.041
Dr. McAndrew:
UH, WE WERE --

18:00.125 --> 18:03.250
WE WERE UNDER THE IMPRESSION
THAT YOU HAD PASSED AWAY.

18:04.792 --> 18:06.750
<i>MENTIROSO!</i>

18:06.834 --> 18:08.709
YOU TOLD THEM I WAS DEAD?

18:08.792 --> 18:13.208
WHAT I MEANT WAS...
SHE'S DEAD TO ME.

18:13.291 --> 18:14.709
<i>AND JUST LIKE THAT,</i>

18:14.792 --> 18:16.709
<i>JORDI'S LIFE BECAME</i>
<i>A TELENOVELA</i>

18:16.792 --> 18:20.458
<i>AND DR. McANDREW'S SEX-CAPADE</i>
<i>BECAME A CAUTIONARY TALE.</i>

18:22.291 --> 18:25.041
WELL, IF I'M DETOXING,
SHOULDN'T I BE IN BED?

18:25.125 --> 18:27.208
WE TRIED THAT,
REMEMBER?

18:27.291 --> 18:30.041
FOR THE RECORD, SPENDING TIME
WITH YOU IS SO DEPRESSING,

18:30.125 --> 18:32.250
IT MAKES ME WANT TO <i>DO</i> DRUGS
NOT <i>QUIT</i> THEM.

18:32.333 --> 18:36.166
OHH. WELL, I HAVE JUST THE THING
TO CHEER YOU UP.

18:38.125 --> 18:39.709
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

18:39.792 --> 18:42.208
UM, LITTLE HUMANS
ARE HIGHLY OVERRATED.

18:42.291 --> 18:44.875
HOW ABOUT I WAIT OUT HERE?
MM!

18:44.959 --> 18:47.333
IF YOU WANT TO SIT AND POUT,
YOU'LL FIT RIGHT IN.

18:55.208 --> 18:56.959
ELSA?

18:57.041 --> 18:59.917
AND WHO ARE YOU --
THE DELUSIONAL SNOWMAN?

19:00.000 --> 19:03.000
YOU MEAN OLAF.
YOU'RE FUNNY. YOU WANT TO PLAY?

19:05.250 --> 19:06.667
[ SIGHS ]

19:06.750 --> 19:08.959
[ High-pitched voice ]
HI.

19:09.041 --> 19:10.667
MY NAME IS...

19:10.750 --> 19:13.000
WHATEVER.

19:13.083 --> 19:15.000
I HAVE SUPER-DRY HAIR,

19:15.083 --> 19:18.667
AND I WORK THE STREETS
SO I CAN SCORE SOME CRACK!

19:18.750 --> 19:20.291
I LOVE THIS STORY!

19:25.333 --> 19:27.291
YO, MAN, I'M ABOUT TO DROP SOME
SERIOUS KNOWLEDGE, ALL RIGHT?

19:27.375 --> 19:29.041
PREPARE
YOUR JAW TO SLACK.

19:29.125 --> 19:31.125
WELL, I CAN'T TALK NOW.
I'M ON A MISSION FOR EMMA.

19:31.208 --> 19:33.458
LOOK, YO,
JULIA CHILD CAN WAIT, MAN.
WHO'S THAT?

19:33.542 --> 19:36.834
ONLY THE SICKEST LADY CHEF
IN HISTORY.

19:36.917 --> 19:38.500
WHATEVER.
I'M SORT OF A FOODIE, BUT...

19:38.583 --> 19:40.333
LOOK, WE HAVE A SITUATION,
ALL RIGHT?

19:40.417 --> 19:42.667
YOUR NEW FRIEND JORDI,
YOUR, UH, SPIRIT ANIMAL,

19:42.750 --> 19:44.166
YOUR BROTHER
FROM ANOTHER MOTHER?

19:44.250 --> 19:45.709
YEAH, WHAT ABOUT HIM?

19:45.792 --> 19:48.291
TURNS OUT HE'S A TWO-FACED,
TWO-LEGGED LYING SACK.

19:48.375 --> 19:50.208
WHAT THE HELL ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT, DASH?

19:51.709 --> 19:54.375
JORDI'S MOM IS ALIVE.

19:56.208 --> 19:58.959
IT WAS MY MOTHER.

19:59.041 --> 20:01.208
SHE POISONED HIM
AGAINST ME.

20:01.291 --> 20:04.375
IT'S OKAY TO LEAVE STUFF BLANK.
JUST FILL OUT WHAT YOU CAN.

20:04.458 --> 20:07.667
BUT I'M HIS MOTHER.
HE IS THE FRUIT OF MY LOOM.

20:07.750 --> 20:08.792
I THINK YOU MEAN LOIN.

20:11.291 --> 20:14.041
FINE.

20:14.125 --> 20:17.375
WHAT ELSE COULD YOU POSSIBLY
NEED TO KNOW?

20:17.458 --> 20:20.333
UH, AN ADDRESS WE CAN VERIFY
TO PROVE THAT HE LIVED WITH YOU.

20:20.417 --> 20:22.166
LIVED WITH ME?
[ CHUCKLES ]

20:22.250 --> 20:24.000
HONEY, I USED TO CALL HIM
MY LITTLE BARNACLE.

20:24.083 --> 20:25.500
HE WOULDN'T LEAVE
MY SIDE.

20:25.583 --> 20:27.583
I EVEN HAD TO TAKE HIM
TO WORK WITH ME.

20:27.667 --> 20:30.500
Dr. McAndrew:
SO, YOU <i>DID</i> GROW UP WITH HER?

20:30.583 --> 20:32.750
OH, YEAH.
YEAH, I GREW UP ALL RIGHT.

20:34.250 --> 20:36.500
SPENT MY 5th BIRTHDAY
IN A CASINO,

20:36.583 --> 20:39.834
MY 6th IN A COCKTAIL LOUNGE
IN RENO.

20:39.917 --> 20:41.750
THE WOMAN IS NOT CAPABLE
OF BEING A MOTHER.

20:41.834 --> 20:45.750
Eva: WE WERE SO CLOSE,
AND EVERY NIGHT,

20:45.834 --> 20:47.917
NO MATTER HOW TIRED I WAS,

20:48.000 --> 20:50.000
I'D MAKE SURE
HE HAD A HOT MEAL.

20:50.083 --> 20:54.542
ANY HOT MEAL I HAD,
I MADE FOR MYSELF,

20:54.625 --> 20:56.208
IF SHE REMEMBERED
TO BRING ME ANYTHING.

20:56.291 --> 20:59.041
SHE WAS ON A REAL STRICT
LIQUID DIET.

20:59.125 --> 21:00.875
Dr. McAndrew: YOU HAVE
EVERY RIGHT TO BE UPSET,

21:00.959 --> 21:02.333
BUT WHETHER
YOU LIKE IT OR NOT...

21:02.417 --> 21:04.750
YOU'RE JORDI'S MOM.
HE NEEDS YOUR SUPPORT.

21:04.834 --> 21:06.208
SO I SUGGEST
THE BOTH OF YOU...

21:06.291 --> 21:07.375
PUT THE PAST BEHIND YOU.

21:07.458 --> 21:08.875
...AND WORK IT OUT.

21:08.959 --> 21:10.917
AND WHAT IF I DON'T
WANT TO WORK IT OUT?

21:12.834 --> 21:15.750
SO, I'LL PUT ALL OF THESE
INTO THE SYSTEM,

21:15.834 --> 21:19.083
AND THEN YOU'LL HAVE TO SIGN
A BUNCH MORE FORMS.

21:19.166 --> 21:21.250
THIS IS A LOT
OF PAPERWORK.

21:21.333 --> 21:24.208
HOW LONG IS HE GONNA BE HERE?
A WEEK?

21:24.291 --> 21:26.875
LONGER, I'M AFRAID.

21:26.959 --> 21:28.375
WHAT THE HELL?

21:28.458 --> 21:31.625
HOW LONG DOES IT TAKE
FOR A BROKEN LEG TO HEAL?

21:34.041 --> 21:36.959
UM...

21:37.041 --> 21:38.959
HE DOESN'T HAVE
A BROKEN LEG.

21:39.041 --> 21:40.959
FRACTURE. WHATEVER.

21:41.041 --> 21:42.959
HOW LONG
TILL I CAN TAKE HIM HOME?

21:46.000 --> 21:49.083
I'M SO SORRY. UH...

21:49.166 --> 21:52.250
WE TOLD JORDI'S GRANDMOTHER.
I -- I THOUGHT YOU KNEW.

21:53.667 --> 21:55.667
JORDI HAS CANCER.

21:59.875 --> 22:00.959
NO.

22:01.041 --> 22:02.458
I'M SORRY.

22:07.625 --> 22:11.041
WHAT DO YOU MEAN JORDI'S MOM
ISN'T DEAD? HOW DO YOU KNOW?

22:11.125 --> 22:14.041
BECAUSE I SAW HER,
LIVE AND IN THE FLESH.

22:14.125 --> 22:16.083
GOOD FLESH,
IF I MIGHT ADD.

22:16.166 --> 22:17.917
SHE'S TAUT, TAN.

22:18.000 --> 22:19.750
OH, MAN,
SHE'S GOING IN THE BANK.

22:19.834 --> 22:21.583
THE THING I DON'T GET
IS WHY?

22:21.667 --> 22:23.917
WHY WOULD HE LIE
ABOUT SOMETHING LIKE THAT?

22:24.000 --> 22:26.583
BECAUSE HE'S A PONZI-SCHEMING
DECEPTICON.

22:26.667 --> 22:29.166
I MEAN, WHO KNOWS WHAT ELSE
HE'S LYING ABOUT?

22:29.250 --> 22:30.500
YOU KNOW,
DOES HE EVEN HAVE CANCER?

22:30.583 --> 22:31.834
IS THAT
HIS REAL HAIR?

22:31.917 --> 22:33.000
IT'S SO SAD.

22:34.166 --> 22:36.041
COME AGAIN?

22:36.125 --> 22:38.875
WELL, THE WHOLE THING.
IT'S TRAGIC.

22:38.959 --> 22:40.917
HOW AWFUL
MUST JORDI'S HOME LIFE BE

22:41.000 --> 22:43.250
FOR HIM TO FEEL THE NEED TO
LIE ABOUT SOMETHING LIKE THIS?

22:43.333 --> 22:45.166
AND CAN YOU IMAGINE
HOW MORTIFIED HE MUST BE

22:45.250 --> 22:47.417
NOW THAT EVERYONE KNOWS
THE TRUTH?

22:49.083 --> 22:50.417
DUDE, SHE'S RIGHT.

22:50.500 --> 22:52.500
HE MUST BE FEELING
PRETTY BAD RIGHT NOW.

22:52.583 --> 22:54.333
[ GROANS ]

22:54.417 --> 22:56.875
ONE OF US SHOULD GO TALK TO HIM,
MAKE SURE EVERYTHING'S OKAY.

22:58.041 --> 23:00.250
I'LL DO IT.

23:01.542 --> 23:03.625
YOU --
SHUT UP.

23:03.709 --> 23:04.917
[ IMITATES
WHIP CRACKING ]

23:05.000 --> 23:07.250
[ GUITAR PLAYING ]

23:07.333 --> 23:08.750
[ DOOR OPENS ]

23:08.834 --> 23:13.375
JORDI?
IS THIS A GOOD TIME?

23:13.458 --> 23:14.709
NO.

23:14.792 --> 23:16.917
PLEASE.
WE NEED TO TALK.

23:19.417 --> 23:21.417
I'M SO NERVOUS.

23:23.709 --> 23:25.458
NO, YOU'RE NOT.

23:25.542 --> 23:26.834
YOU HAVE NERVES
OF STEEL.

23:26.917 --> 23:28.709
YOU ALWAYS KNOW
EXACTLY WHAT YOU WANT.

23:28.792 --> 23:31.291
SO, WHAT'S YOUR ANGLE
THIS TIME, HUH?

23:31.375 --> 23:33.709
'CAUSE I KNOW YOU HAVE ONE.
<i>¿QUE QUIERES, MAMá?</i>

23:33.792 --> 23:35.458
<i>DíGAME.</i>

23:39.000 --> 23:41.417
<i>SOLAMENTE QUEIRO ESTAR</i>
<i>AQUIPARA AYUDARTE.</i>

23:41.500 --> 23:44.917
YOU'RE MY SON...

23:45.000 --> 23:46.917
AND YOU'RE SICK.

23:47.000 --> 23:50.417
SICK?
I HAVE CANCER, MOM.

23:50.500 --> 23:53.417
CANCER.
YOU KNOW WHAT THAT MEANS?

23:53.500 --> 23:55.417
THIS ISN'T AN EARACHE OR --
OR THE SNIFFLES,

23:55.500 --> 23:56.750
WHERE YOU CAN JUST GIVE ME
SOME <i>Té CON LIMóN</i>

23:56.834 --> 23:58.583
AND SEND ME
BACK TO SCHOOL.

23:58.667 --> 24:00.333
I COULD DIE.

24:02.000 --> 24:05.417
YEAH. I KNOW HOW SERIOUS
THIS IS.

24:05.500 --> 24:08.000
ABUELA DIDN'T, AND THAT'S
WHO YOU DUMPED ME WITH.

24:08.083 --> 24:10.667
AND NOW YOU WANT BACK
IN MY LIFE?

24:10.750 --> 24:13.750
NO. [ SCOFFS ]
I DON'T THINK SO.

24:14.834 --> 24:18.250
I'M SORRY.

24:18.333 --> 24:20.291
LOOK,
I KNOW YOU'RE ANGRY,

24:20.375 --> 24:21.792
BUT MAYBE THIS HAPPENED
FOR A REASON.

24:21.875 --> 24:23.333
MAYBE THIS IS GOD'S WAY
OF ALLOWING US

24:23.417 --> 24:25.792
TO FIX THINGS BETWEEN US.

24:25.875 --> 24:27.458
YOU CAN'T FIX THIS.

24:27.542 --> 24:29.125
THE ONLY PERSON THAT CAN
HELP ME NOW IS DR. McANDREW,

24:29.208 --> 24:32.041
SO IF YOU REALLY WANT
WHAT'S BEST FOR ME,

24:32.125 --> 24:33.500
SIGN THE PAPERS
TO EMANCIPATE ME

24:33.583 --> 24:36.208
AND THEN DO WHAT
YOU DO BEST -- LEAVE.

24:38.625 --> 24:40.709
YOU'RE STUBBORN.

24:42.583 --> 24:44.834
THAT'S ONE TRAIT
YOU INHERITED FROM ME.

24:48.709 --> 24:49.792
YOU KNOW WHAT?

24:49.875 --> 24:51.375
WHEN YOU WERE LITTLE,

24:51.458 --> 24:53.875
THE ONLY WAY WE COULD RESOLVE
OUR DISAGREEMENTS

24:53.959 --> 24:55.667
WAS WITH A LITTLE
FRIENDLY COMPETITION.

24:58.625 --> 25:01.875
[ CHUCKLES ]

25:02.000 --> 25:03.750
FINE.

25:03.834 --> 25:08.208
WHEN I WIN,
YOU SIGN THE FORMS AND LEAVE.

25:08.291 --> 25:10.709
AND IF I WIN, I GET TO STICK
AROUND AND BE YOUR MOM.

25:10.792 --> 25:14.750
<i>FAMILY GAME NIGHT JUST TOOK ON</i>
<i>A WHOLE NEW MEANING.</i>

25:14.834 --> 25:15.917
AND ONE MORE.

25:16.000 --> 25:17.750
[ BLOWS ]
THAT'S IT.

25:17.834 --> 25:19.750
ALL DONE.

25:19.834 --> 25:24.417
SO WHAT'S IT GOING TO BE TODAY,
SPIDERS OR DRAGONS?

25:24.500 --> 25:25.667
DRAGONS.

25:25.750 --> 25:27.500
SPEAKING OF DRAGONS,

25:27.583 --> 25:31.834
OUR FRIEND SIMMI
SEEMS TO HAVE TAMED ONE.

25:31.917 --> 25:35.000
YEAH, THEY BRING THE YELLOW
PILLS JUST BEFORE DINNER.

25:35.083 --> 25:38.166
Kara: DO YOU EVER
GET THE BLUE PILLS?

25:38.250 --> 25:40.875
THOSE COME AT BEDTIME,
AROUND 9:00.
PERFECT.

25:40.959 --> 25:43.875
I'LL BE BY THEN,
OKAY?

25:44.000 --> 25:45.583
I DON'T KNOW.
I LIKE BLUE.

25:45.667 --> 25:47.917
FOR A BLUE. YOU GOT TO BRAID
MY DOLL'S HAIR, TOO.

25:48.000 --> 25:50.250
WELL, THAT WASN'T THE DEAL,
MUFFIN FACE.

25:50.333 --> 25:52.250
TAKE IT OR LEAVE IT,
STUPID FACE.

25:52.333 --> 25:53.792
SHE'S GONNA LEAVE IT!

25:54.625 --> 25:57.542
GET UP! GET UP.

25:57.625 --> 25:59.166
OW! OW!
YOU'RE HURTING ME!

25:59.250 --> 26:02.041
LOW EVEN FOR YOU,
TAKING DRUGS FROM A SICK CHILD.

26:02.125 --> 26:04.208
WELL, APPARENTLY,
I'M A DRUG ADDICT

26:04.291 --> 26:05.667
WHO WOULD DO WHATEVER IT TAKES
TO GET HIGH.

26:05.750 --> 26:07.208
I MEAN, HAVE YOU EVER SEEN
"BREAKING BAD,"

26:07.291 --> 26:08.709
OR CAN YOU NOT AFFORD
BASIC CABLE?

26:08.792 --> 26:10.041
I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHY I TRY.

26:10.125 --> 26:11.709
YEAH, I DON'T,
EITHER!

26:11.792 --> 26:13.959
I MEAN, WHAT DO YOU CARE
IF I FAIL MY STUPID DRUG TEST?

26:14.041 --> 26:15.583
I DON'T.

26:15.667 --> 26:18.041
IN FACT, YOU WANT THEM?
HERE, HERE. TAKE THEM!

26:18.125 --> 26:19.375
DO WHATEVER THE HELL
YOU WANT TO DO.

26:19.458 --> 26:21.792
[ PILLS CLATTER ]

26:24.458 --> 26:26.917
YEAH...

26:27.000 --> 26:29.000
I'M PRETTY SURE
SHE DIDN'T MEAN THAT.

26:32.750 --> 26:34.834
YO, YOU'RE SHORT $50,
MAN.

26:34.917 --> 26:37.834
YOU SAID YOU HAD $200
ON JORDI-THE-HIJO.

26:37.917 --> 26:40.500
YEAH, I WAS KIND OF HOPING
YOU COULD SPOT ME FOR THE REST.

26:40.583 --> 26:42.333
SPOT YOU?

26:42.417 --> 26:44.417
WHAT DO I LOOK LIKE --
GOLDMAN DASH?

26:44.500 --> 26:46.500
COME ON, MAN.
I'M GOOD FOR IT.

26:46.583 --> 26:48.500
STOP WASTING MY TIME,
HOMEY, ALL RIGHT?

26:48.583 --> 26:50.000
WE IN A HOSPITAL.

26:50.083 --> 26:51.166
YOU COULD DROP DEAD TOMORROW
FOR ALL I KNOW.

26:51.250 --> 26:52.625
WHERE DOES THAT
LEAVE ME?

26:52.709 --> 26:54.625
I ONLY HAD
GALL-BLADDER SURGERY,

26:54.709 --> 26:58.000
AND IT WAS LAPAROSCOPIC.

26:58.083 --> 27:00.417
WHAT DO YOU THINK
YOU'RE DOING?

27:00.500 --> 27:02.250
I'M JUST HARD CHILLING.
WHAT'S GOING ON, MAN?

27:02.333 --> 27:04.417
CHILLING WITH COLD,
HARD CASH.

27:04.500 --> 27:05.834
CASH FROM BETS
YOU'RE TAKING

27:05.917 --> 27:07.959
ON A CERTAIN
MOTHER-vs.-SON COMPETITION?

27:08.041 --> 27:09.458
NOTHING WRONG WITH
A LITTLE HUSTLE JUST TO,

27:09.542 --> 27:11.041
YOU KNOW,
KEEP THE BLOOD FLOWING.

27:11.125 --> 27:14.125
EXCEPT THAT GAMBLING IS ILLEGAL
AND IMMORAL

27:14.208 --> 27:15.375
AND AGAINST THE RULES.

27:15.458 --> 27:17.083
How much to get in
on the action?

27:17.166 --> 27:20.333
FOR SERIOUS, OR IS THIS SOME
NURSE JACKSON-STYLE SHAKEDOWN?

27:20.417 --> 27:22.792
COME ON. GIVE ME $50
ON E. PALACIOS FOR THE WIN.

27:22.875 --> 27:24.667
MY MONEY'S ON MAMA.

27:24.750 --> 27:26.375
THAT'S WHAT
I'M TALKING ABOUT.
ALL RIGHT.

27:26.458 --> 27:30.041
DON'T LET ME DOWN NOW.
BABY NEEDS A NEW PAIR OF KICKS.

27:34.208 --> 27:37.792
DR. McANDREW.

27:37.875 --> 27:39.125
ADAM.

27:39.208 --> 27:42.125
YEAH, UM,
DO YOU HAVE A MINUTE?

27:42.208 --> 27:44.500
YEAH. YEAH.

27:47.709 --> 27:51.667
SO, UH,
JUST TO BE CLEAR,

27:51.750 --> 27:54.917
AS FAR AS JORDI'S CONCERNED,
THIS THING BETWEEN US --
NEVER HAPPENED.

27:55.000 --> 27:57.417
I MEAN, HONESTLY,
IF I'D KNOWN WHO YOU WERE...

27:58.917 --> 28:02.000
I CARE ABOUT YOUR SON,
AND FROM WHAT HE JUST TOLD ME --
[ CHUCKLES ]

28:02.083 --> 28:04.834
I'M SURE HE PICTURED ME
QUITE AS THE WITCH.

28:04.917 --> 28:06.834
MY SON
LIKES TO EMBELLISH.

28:06.917 --> 28:10.208
HIS FAVORITE BEDTIME STORY
WAS "PINOCCHIO."

28:10.291 --> 28:13.166
SO, WHY DON'T YOU TELL ME
YOUR SIDE OF THE STORY?

28:13.250 --> 28:15.667
YOU MEAN,
HOW HIS DAD HIT THE ROAD

28:15.750 --> 28:18.000
THE SECOND HE FOUND OUT
I WAS PREGNANT?

28:18.083 --> 28:19.667
I WAS 19.

28:19.750 --> 28:22.333
I WAS ALONE AND BROKE
AND IN A STRANGE COUNTRY.

28:22.417 --> 28:25.166
I DID WHAT I HAD TO DO
TO SURVIVE.

28:25.250 --> 28:27.166
AND I MAY NOT HAVE BEEN
THE WORLD'S BEST MOM,

28:27.250 --> 28:28.750
BUT I'M STILL HIS MOTHER.

28:28.834 --> 28:32.208
AND IF HE'S SICK,
I WANT TO BE HERE FOR HIM.

28:32.291 --> 28:35.208
HE TRUSTS YOU.

28:35.291 --> 28:37.875
CAN YOU TALK TO HIM,

28:37.959 --> 28:41.375
MAYBE TELL HIM
TO GIVE ME A CHANCE?

28:57.959 --> 29:00.709
WHAT ARE
YOU LOOKING FOR?

29:00.792 --> 29:02.542
A WAY TO GET RID
OF MY MOTHER.

29:02.625 --> 29:05.208
[ CHUCKLES ] OKAY.

29:05.291 --> 29:07.542
ALTHOUGH, I DON'T THINK LEO
KEEPS SHIVS IN THERE.

29:07.625 --> 29:09.542
<i>NOPE, JUST PORN.</i>

29:09.625 --> 29:14.083
I JUST NEED...
A DECK OF CARDS.

29:14.166 --> 29:15.834
WE'VE GOT A WAGER
FOR MY LIFE.

29:20.834 --> 29:23.083
[ SIGHS ]

29:23.166 --> 29:25.750
MAYBE YOUR MOM BEING HERE
IS ACTUALLY A GOOD THING.

29:25.834 --> 29:29.834
RIGHT, SHE'S HERE BECAUSE
SHE WANTS TO HELP YOU.

29:29.917 --> 29:32.417
AND HONESTLY, YOU'RE GONNA DO
MUCH BETTER IF SHE'S AROUND.

29:32.500 --> 29:33.834
TRUST ME, I WON'T.

29:33.917 --> 29:35.417
JORDI, YOU GOT A LONG ROAD
AHEAD OF YOU.

29:35.500 --> 29:38.083
YOU HAVE CHEMO.
YOU HAVE MORE SURGERIES.

29:38.166 --> 29:40.291
RESEARCH, AS WELL AS
MY PERSONAL EXPERIENCE,

29:40.375 --> 29:43.291
SHOWS THAT PATIENTS HAVE
A MUCH BETTER CHANCE OF SURVIVAL

29:43.375 --> 29:45.417
WHEN THEY HAVE SOMEONE
CLOSE TO THEM BY THEIR SIDE.

29:45.500 --> 29:47.417
I HAVE YOU.

29:47.500 --> 29:50.834
I'M NOT YOUR FAMILY.

29:58.709 --> 30:00.291
SO, DID YOU TALK
TO JORDI?

30:00.375 --> 30:03.375
HIS MOM WAS IN THERE.
I DIDN'T WANT TO BUG HIM.

30:03.458 --> 30:04.875
DON'T TOUCH THOSE!

30:04.959 --> 30:06.375
THEY MUST BE COOL BY NOW.

30:06.458 --> 30:08.208
OH, I THOUGHT THEY WERE
FOR KINDERGARTNERS.

30:08.291 --> 30:10.834
THEY ARE, BUT, GOD,
THEY LOOK GOOD.
YOU'RE SO IMPATIENT.

30:10.917 --> 30:12.500
EVEN DURING CHEMO,

30:12.583 --> 30:14.792
YOU USED TO TRY AND SPEED IT UP
BY RELEASING THE TIMER.

30:14.875 --> 30:18.291
YOU'D GIVE YOURSELF
TWICE THE DOSE IN HALF THE TIME,

30:18.375 --> 30:20.959
AND THEN YOU'D GET SICK
AND REGRET IT.

30:21.041 --> 30:22.792
YOU'RE RIGHT.
I'M VERY IMPULSIVE.

30:22.875 --> 30:26.792
TRUST ME...I KNOW.

30:26.875 --> 30:29.625
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT US?

30:29.709 --> 30:34.458
NO. FORGET IT.
IT DOESN'T MATTER.

30:34.542 --> 30:36.834
NO, IT <i>DOES</i> MATTER.

30:36.917 --> 30:38.375
I WAS IMPULSIVE

30:38.458 --> 30:41.083
AND I BROKE THINGS OFF
AND I REGRETTED IT.

30:42.500 --> 30:43.750
YOU REGRETTED IT?

30:43.834 --> 30:45.834
I WAS AN IDIOT.

30:45.917 --> 30:47.667
I WAS SCARED.

30:47.750 --> 30:49.125
AFTER MY SURGERY,
I THOUGHT I WAS GONNA DIE.

30:49.208 --> 30:50.500
I DIDN'T WANT TO PUT YOU
THROUGH THAT.

30:52.917 --> 30:55.166
THAT'S WHY
YOU THINK WE BROKE UP?

30:55.250 --> 30:57.667
I <i>KNOW</i> THAT'S WHY WE BROKE UP.
I'M THE ONE WHO DID IT.
[ CHUCKLES ]

30:57.750 --> 30:59.166
WHAT'S SO FUNNY?
YOU'RE FUNNY.

30:59.250 --> 31:01.000
YOU WEREN'T AFRAID
YOU WERE GONNA DIE, LEO.

31:01.083 --> 31:02.542
YOU WERE AFRAID
YOU WERE GONNA <i>LIVE.</i>

31:02.625 --> 31:04.166
NO, I'M PRETTY SURE
I WAS AFRAID OF DYING.

31:04.250 --> 31:06.375
YOU DUMPED ME
BECAUSE I DON'T FIT THE PROFILE

31:06.458 --> 31:07.875
OF YOUR IDEAL GIRLFRIEND.

31:07.959 --> 31:10.208
I'M NOT BLONDE
AND POPULAR

31:10.291 --> 31:12.542
AND WORRIED ABOUT WHAT PARTY
I'M GOING TO THIS WEEKEND.

31:12.625 --> 31:15.125
IN OUR REAL LIVES, YOU WOULDN'T
EVEN <i>LOOK</i> AT A GIRL LIKE ME,

31:15.208 --> 31:16.583
LET ALONE DATE ME,

31:16.667 --> 31:18.542
AND YOU WERE AFRAID
THAT IF YOU LIVED,

31:18.625 --> 31:20.208
YOU'D BE STUCK WITH ME.

31:20.291 --> 31:23.709
THAT'S NOT FAIR.
IT'S NOT TRUE.

31:23.792 --> 31:25.542
WHY CAN'T YOU ADMIT IT?

31:25.625 --> 31:29.041
I LIKED YOU SO MUCH MORE
THAN YOU LIKED ME.

31:29.125 --> 31:31.041
I KNEW IT, YOU KNEW IT,

31:31.125 --> 31:33.709
EVERYONE IN THIS FREAKING PLACE
KNEW IT, LEO.

31:33.792 --> 31:35.709
THAT'S WHY WE BROKE UP.

31:46.500 --> 31:48.166
SHE JUST LOST IT
ON ME.

31:48.250 --> 31:49.750
WHAT DID SHE SAY?

31:49.834 --> 31:51.959
I DON'T EVEN KNOW.
THE WHOLE THING MADE NO SENSE.

31:52.041 --> 31:53.417
HEY.

31:55.625 --> 31:57.542
YOU MIGHT BE RIGHT
ABOUT HIM.

31:57.625 --> 31:58.875
SAY MORE.

31:59.000 --> 32:00.583
YOU KNOW,
MAYBE HE'S THE PROBLEM.

32:00.667 --> 32:02.375
FIRST HE TRIES
TO GET BETWEEN US,

32:02.458 --> 32:04.417
WHICH WOULD NEVER HAPPEN,
OBVIOUSLY.
OBVIOUSLY.

32:04.500 --> 32:06.542
THEN HE'S STARTS
MANIPULATING EMMA,

32:06.625 --> 32:08.041
TELLING HER SOME SOB STORY
ABOUT HIS DEAD MOM.

32:08.125 --> 32:09.583
THAT'S WHAT
I'VE BEEN SAYING, MAN!

32:09.667 --> 32:11.250
YOU'RE RIGHT.

32:11.333 --> 32:13.250
YOU'RE RIGHT.

32:13.333 --> 32:16.250
WHAT IS GOING ON?

32:16.333 --> 32:18.625
HEY. YOU WANT TO PLAY A GAME?
I'M A LITTLE RUSTY.

32:18.709 --> 32:20.875
WHAT'S GAME IS THAT --
LIAR'S POKER?

32:22.000 --> 32:23.542
WHAT'S YOUR PROBLEM?

32:23.625 --> 32:25.959
YOU. WE TRUSTED YOU.
WE BECAME YOUR FRIENDS.

32:26.041 --> 32:27.625
NOW WE DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHO YOU ARE.

32:27.709 --> 32:30.709
RULE NUMBER ONE -- NEVER LIE
TO A FELLOW RED BANDER, MAN.

32:32.291 --> 32:33.709
WHAT, YOU THINK
IT DOESN'T MATTER?

32:33.792 --> 32:35.083
IT'S ALL THAT MATTERS.

32:35.166 --> 32:38.583
SO, I LIED. BIG DEAL.
WE ALL LIE.

32:38.667 --> 32:40.917
EMMA LIES TO GET SKINNY,
DASH LIES TO GET POT,

32:41.041 --> 32:42.166
YOU LIE TO GET OUT OF P.T.

32:42.250 --> 32:45.125
AT LEAST I LIED
TO SAVE MY LIFE.

32:47.083 --> 32:49.250
HE KIND OF HAS A POINT,
MAN.

32:59.041 --> 33:00.625
WHAT?

33:00.709 --> 33:02.959
JUST CURIOUS WHAT
THE WOMEN'S SIDE LOOKS LIKE.

33:03.041 --> 33:04.583
<i>ANOTHER LIE.</i>

33:04.667 --> 33:07.208
<i>THE GUY'S BEEN DOING IT</i>
<i>SINCE HIGH SCHOOL.</i>

33:13.041 --> 33:14.291
YOU OKAY?

33:14.375 --> 33:15.625
DO I LOOK OKAY?
NO.

33:15.709 --> 33:17.125
THEN DON'T ASK
STUPID QUESTIONS.

33:17.208 --> 33:20.625
OH, OKAY,
HERE'S A BETTER ONE --

33:20.709 --> 33:23.208
WHY HAVE YOU BEEN TORTURING
YOURSELF ALL DAY?

33:23.291 --> 33:24.542
IT'S NOT LIKE
YOUR JOB DEPENDS

33:24.625 --> 33:26.041
ON WHETHER
MISS THING PEES CLEAN.

33:26.125 --> 33:29.208
[ SIGHS ]

33:29.291 --> 33:31.208
I MESSED UP.

33:31.291 --> 33:33.041
I TOLD KARA
SHE COULD INVITE A FRIEND,

33:33.125 --> 33:34.625
EVEN THOUGH I KNEW
IT WAS STUPID,

33:34.709 --> 33:37.333
BUT I DID IT SO SHE WOULD
SHUT THE HELL UP.

33:37.417 --> 33:41.333
AND THEN HER HEART MONITOR
WENT OFF, AND...

33:41.417 --> 33:45.166
IT WAS MY FAULT.

33:45.250 --> 33:48.166
SO, I THOUGHT
IF WE SPENT THE DAY TOGETHER,

33:48.250 --> 33:50.667
I MIGHT FIND ONE THING
NOT TO HATE ABOUT HER.

33:50.750 --> 33:53.500
I JUST NEED ONE THING,
SOME SHRED OF HUMANITY.

33:53.583 --> 33:55.709
BECAUSE RIGHT NOW,
I HATE HER SO DAMN MUCH

33:55.792 --> 33:58.375
I'M AFRAID ONE DAY
I WON'T ANSWER HER CALL BUTTON

33:58.458 --> 34:01.375
JUST TO SPITE HER.

34:01.458 --> 34:03.208
AND THEN MAYBE
SHE REALLY WILL END UP DEAD,

34:03.291 --> 34:05.000
AND IT'LL BE ON ME.

34:05.083 --> 34:06.834
YOU WOULDN'T DO THAT.

34:06.917 --> 34:08.041
YOU DON'T KNOW THAT.

34:08.125 --> 34:11.834
YEAH, I DO.
I KNOW YOU, DENA.

34:11.917 --> 34:14.709
YOU GAVE UP A LIFE
THAT MOST PEOPLE ONLY DREAM OF

34:14.792 --> 34:19.500
TO BE HERE,
TO HELP PEOPLE.

34:19.583 --> 34:21.917
THAT'S JUST
WHO YOU ARE.

34:26.291 --> 34:28.208
AND I'M NOT SAYING KARA
ISN'T ROTTEN TO THE CORE.

34:28.291 --> 34:30.041
[ CHUCKLES ]
MAYBE SHE IS.

34:30.125 --> 34:32.709
BUT SHE DID DO ONE THING RIGHT.
[ SIGHS ]

34:32.792 --> 34:34.417
SHE PEED CLEAN.

34:38.333 --> 34:40.000
[ SIGHS ]

34:42.166 --> 34:45.000
<i>WELCOME TO THE PALACIOS</i>
<i>POKER NIGHT.</i>

34:45.083 --> 34:47.792
<i>AS IF THE STAKES</i>
<i>AREN'T HIGH ENOUGH,</i>

34:47.875 --> 34:49.709
<i>THEY'RE ALSO PLAYING</i>
<i>FOR JELLYBEANS.</i>

34:49.792 --> 34:53.125
LET ME KNOW
IF YOU SEE THE WARDEN.

34:56.959 --> 35:00.542
DO YOU HAVE ANY 7s?
♪ IT WAS EARLY MORNING
YESTERDAY ♪

35:00.625 --> 35:02.208
GO FISH.

35:02.291 --> 35:03.875
Eva: THERE YOU GO.
♪ I WAS UP BEFORE THE DAWN ♪

35:03.959 --> 35:06.208
JORDI'S SISTER REALLY KNOWS
HOW TO HANDLE A DECK.

35:06.291 --> 35:07.375
Leo:
THAT'S HIS MOTHER.

35:07.458 --> 35:10.250
WOW!

35:10.333 --> 35:12.750
NOTE TO SELF --
ASK ABOUT <i>HER</i> SKIN-CARE REGIMEN.
♪ AND I REALLY HAVE
ENJOYED MY STAY ♪

35:12.834 --> 35:14.750
YOU DON'T MIND ROLLING UP
YOUR SLEEVES

35:14.834 --> 35:16.250
A LITTLE MORE, DO YOU?
♪ BUT I MUST BE MOVING ON ♪

35:16.333 --> 35:19.291
REALLY?
YOU DON'T TRUST ME?

35:19.375 --> 35:21.792
♪ LIKE A KING WITHOUT A CASTLE ♪

35:21.875 --> 35:24.250
♪ LIKE A QUEEN
WITHOUT A THRONE ♪

35:24.333 --> 35:28.125
♪ I'M AN EARLY-MORNING LOVER,
AND I MUST BE MOVING ON ♪

35:28.208 --> 35:30.000
♪ YEAH, YEAH ♪

35:32.166 --> 35:34.583
♪ NOW I BELIEVE
IN WHAT YOU SAY ♪

35:34.667 --> 35:38.250
♪ IS THE UNDISPUTED TRUTH ♪

35:38.333 --> 35:39.834
YOU SURE, JO-JO?

35:39.917 --> 35:41.458
JUST HIT ME, MOM.

35:41.542 --> 35:45.583
♪ BUT I HAVE TO HAVE THINGS
MY OWN WAY ♪

35:45.667 --> 35:49.166
♪ TO KEEP ME IN MY YOUTH ♪

35:49.250 --> 35:53.583
♪ LIKE A SHIP WITHOUT AN ANCHOR,
LIKE A SLAVE WITHOUT A CHAIN ♪

35:53.667 --> 35:56.083
♪ JUST THE THOUGHT
OF THOSE SWEET LADIES ♪

35:56.166 --> 35:58.917
♪ SENDS A SHIVER
THROUGH MY VEINS ♪
I RAISE YOU FIVE.

35:59.000 --> 36:01.125
♪ AND I WILL GO ON SHINING,
SHINING LIKE BRAND-NEW ♪

36:01.208 --> 36:02.583
♪ I'LL NEVER LOOK BEHIND ME ♪

36:02.667 --> 36:03.792
CAREFUL.

36:03.875 --> 36:05.917
♪ MY TROUBLES WILL BE FEW ♪

36:06.000 --> 36:07.417
YOU'RE BITING YOUR LIP.

36:10.917 --> 36:13.834
DON'T BITE YOUR LIP.
THAT'S YOUR TELL.

36:13.917 --> 36:16.959
I'M NEVER
GONNA GET THIS.

36:17.041 --> 36:19.542
OF COURSE YOU WILL.
JUST TRY THIS.

36:22.792 --> 36:27.041
♪ GOODBYE, STRANGER,
IT'S BEEN NICE ♪

36:27.125 --> 36:30.375
♪ HOPE YOU'LL FIND
YOUR PARADISE ♪

36:30.458 --> 36:31.875
I'M ALL-IN.

36:31.959 --> 36:34.542
♪ TRIED TO SEE YOUR
POINT OF VIEW ♪

36:34.625 --> 36:38.208
♪ HOPE YOUR DREAMS
WILL ALL COME TRUE ♪

36:38.291 --> 36:42.041
♪ GOODBYE, MARY, GOODBYE, JANE ♪

36:42.125 --> 36:45.291
♪ WILL WE EVER MEET AGAIN? ♪

36:45.375 --> 36:49.291
♪ FEEL NO SORROW,
FEEL NO SHAME ♪

36:49.375 --> 36:51.834
♪ COME TOMORROW, FEEL NO PAIN ♪

36:51.917 --> 36:53.750
♪ AND SWEET DEVOTION ♪

36:53.834 --> 36:55.417
♪ GOODBYE, MARY, GOODBYE, JANE ♪
♪ IT'S NOT FOR ME ♪

36:55.500 --> 36:57.750
I FOLD.
♪ JUST GIVE ME MOTION ♪

36:57.834 --> 36:59.083
♪ WILL WE EVER ♪
♪ AND SET ME FREE ♪

36:59.166 --> 37:01.000
♪ MEET AGAIN? ♪

37:01.083 --> 37:02.542
♪ FEEL NO SORROW ♪
♪ AND THE LAND AND THE OCEAN ♪

37:02.625 --> 37:04.333
♪ FEEL NO SHAME ♪
♪ FAR AWAY ♪

37:04.417 --> 37:05.917
IT'S THAT LIP.
♪ THE LIFE I'VE CHOSEN ♪

37:06.000 --> 37:07.875
♪ COME TOMORROW ♪
♪ EVERY DAY ♪

37:07.959 --> 37:09.583
♪ FEEL NO PAIN ♪
I CAN ALWAYS TELL
WHEN YOU'RE BLUFFING.

37:09.667 --> 37:11.083
♪ GOODBYE, MARY ♪
♪ SO GOODBYE, MARY ♪

37:11.166 --> 37:12.709
GOOD GAME, MOM.
♪ GOODBYE, JANE ♪

37:12.792 --> 37:14.291
♪ GOODBYE, JANE ♪
♪ WILL WE EVER ♪

37:14.375 --> 37:15.166
♪ WILL WE EVER ♪
♪ MEET AGAIN? ♪

37:15.250 --> 37:17.375
♪ MEET AGAIN? ♪

37:20.417 --> 37:22.709
[ WHISTLING ]

37:29.750 --> 37:32.333
SO?

37:32.417 --> 37:36.542
IS MY PEE AS CLEAN
AS A MORMON VARIETY SHOW?

37:36.625 --> 37:38.208
YOU PASSED
YOUR DRUG TEST.

37:38.291 --> 37:40.041
YOU'RE NOT
A TOTAL CRIMINAL.

37:40.125 --> 37:41.709
GOOD FOR YOU.

37:41.792 --> 37:43.750
DON'T YOU THINK
YOU OWE ME AN APOLOGY?

37:44.959 --> 37:47.709
SWEETIE, IT'LL BE
A COLD DAY IN HELL

37:47.792 --> 37:50.458
BEFORE I APOLOGIZE TO ANYONE
FOR DOING MY JOB.

37:57.125 --> 37:58.709
BUT YOU <i>DID</i>
SURPRISE ME,

37:58.792 --> 38:01.208
AND I'M NEVER SURPRISED.

38:01.291 --> 38:03.625
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

38:23.000 --> 38:25.000
[ SIREN WAILS IN DISTANCE ]

38:28.083 --> 38:30.000
HEY.

38:31.834 --> 38:33.083
HEY.

38:33.166 --> 38:36.917
LOOK, I'M SORRY
I UPSET YOU.

38:37.000 --> 38:38.250
I'M SORRY, TOO.

38:38.333 --> 38:40.959
I OVERREACTED.
NO, IT WAS MY FAULT.

38:41.041 --> 38:43.125
I MADE A LOT OF MISTAKES
WHEN WE WERE TOGETHER,

38:43.208 --> 38:45.000
BUT I WANT TO MAKE IT UP
TO YOU.

38:46.417 --> 38:48.333
I THINK
WE CAN MAKE THINGS WORK.

38:49.917 --> 38:52.000
SO DO I.

38:52.083 --> 38:55.417
YOU DO?

38:55.500 --> 38:57.709
WE CAN'T STAY MAD
AT EACH OTHER FOREVER, RIGHT?

38:57.792 --> 39:01.542
I'M READY TO PUT THE PAST
BEHIND US IF YOU ARE.

39:01.625 --> 39:02.834
FRIENDS?

39:04.458 --> 39:05.709
FRIENDS.

39:05.792 --> 39:07.667
THAT'S WHAT YOU MEANT,
RIGHT?

39:07.750 --> 39:09.667
YEAH.

39:09.750 --> 39:11.125
EXACTLY WHAT
I WAS GONNA SAY.

39:11.208 --> 39:12.959
[ COASTS' "OCEANS" PLAYS ]

39:13.041 --> 39:16.000
IT'S PROBABLY WHAT WE SHOULD
HAVE BEEN ALL ALONG, YOU KNOW?

39:17.959 --> 39:20.959
NOW WE CAN BE
IN EACH OTHER'S LIVES FOREVER.

39:23.083 --> 39:24.166
SURE.

39:24.250 --> 39:28.500
♪ WE FELL IN LOVE ♪

39:28.583 --> 39:31.917
♪ RIGHT BY THE OCEAN ♪

39:37.750 --> 39:39.542
HEY, STRANGER.

39:39.625 --> 39:41.375
HEY.

39:41.458 --> 39:44.500
UM,
I'LL BE RIGHT THERE.

39:44.583 --> 39:47.583
SO, I HEAR YOU'RE STICKING
AROUND FOR A WHILE.

39:47.667 --> 39:49.834
IT LOOKS THAT WAY.

39:49.917 --> 39:51.333
IT'S THE BEST THING
FOR JORDI.

39:51.417 --> 39:54.250
WELL, I'M VERY GRATEFUL
HE'S IN SUCH GOOD HANDS.

40:09.166 --> 40:12.000
IDIOT.

40:14.750 --> 40:16.667
HEY, JO-JO.

40:16.750 --> 40:18.667
ARE YOU HUNGRY?

40:18.750 --> 40:20.166
I CAN RUN DOWN
TO THE CAFETERIA

40:20.250 --> 40:22.375
AND GET YOU
ONE OF THOSE MINI PIZZAS.

40:22.458 --> 40:24.542
THAT'S OKAY.

40:24.625 --> 40:27.083
[ SIGHS ]
I KNOW.

40:27.166 --> 40:29.750
WHAT ABOUT
SOME ROOT-BEER FLOATS?

40:29.834 --> 40:32.250
ARE YOU SERIOUSLY
TRYING TO BE A MOM NOW?

40:32.333 --> 40:34.709
DOES IT BOTHER YOU?

40:36.500 --> 40:38.083
I CAN'T TELL YET.

40:38.166 --> 40:40.542
HEY, JORDI.

40:40.625 --> 40:42.709
JO-JO...

40:42.792 --> 40:45.041
YOU DIDN'T TELL ME
YOU HAD A GIRLFRIEND.
MOM.

40:46.291 --> 40:48.083
HEY.

40:48.166 --> 40:51.417
I DIDN'T MEAN TO INTERRUPT.
I WAS JUST DROPPING THOSE OFF.

40:51.500 --> 40:52.875
OH, THAT'S VERY SWEET.

40:52.959 --> 40:55.375
I'M EVA.
I'M JORDI'S MOM.

40:55.458 --> 40:57.041
EMMA.
NICE TO MEET YOU.

40:57.125 --> 41:00.709
NICE TO MEET YOU, TOO.
THAT LOOKS YUMMY.

41:00.792 --> 41:03.000
[ BLOWS KISS ]
SEE YOU TOMORROW.

41:05.333 --> 41:07.417
SHE ACTUALLY SEEMS
KIND OF NICE.

41:07.500 --> 41:08.917
YEAH,
DON'T GET USED TO IT.

41:09.000 --> 41:10.667
I'M STILL TO FIGURE OUT A WAY
TO GET RID OF HER.

41:10.750 --> 41:12.834
MAYBE YOU SHOULDN'T
HAVE LET HER WIN, THEN.

41:14.041 --> 41:16.166
I SAW YOU FOLD
WITH A FULL HOUSE.

41:16.250 --> 41:18.000
I DON'T KNOW
WHETHER TO BE EMBARRASSED

41:18.083 --> 41:19.750
OR FLATTERED
THAT YOU NOTICED.

41:19.834 --> 41:21.917
DON'T BE EMBARRASSED.

41:22.000 --> 41:24.250
EVERYONE WANTS THEIR MOM
WHEN THEY'RE SICK.

41:24.333 --> 41:27.750
♪ WE FELL IN LOVE ♪

41:27.834 --> 41:30.667
♪ RIGHT BY THE OCEAN ♪

41:32.166 --> 41:35.417
<i>THAT'S THE THING ABOUT LIES --</i>

41:35.500 --> 41:38.250
<i>EVEN IF YOU'RE TELLING THEM</i>
<i>FOR THE RIGHT REASONS,</i>

41:38.333 --> 41:42.917
<i>THE PERSON WHO USUALLY WINDS UP</i>
<i>GETTING HURT IS YOU.</i>
♪ MADE ALL OUR PLANS ♪

41:43.041 --> 41:46.000
♪ DOWN ON THE SAND ♪

42:02.250 --> 42:05.250
